NOTE: This project was a very fast project made almost exclusevly using AI for some twitch streams.

Exact environment bootstrap:

./start.sh

The setup script recreates the project's local `.venv` with the exact package versions currently in use and verifies the Python files compile.
If Python 3.13.3 is not auto-detected on a machine, run `PYTHON_BIN=/path/to/python3.13 ./start.sh`.

Manual setup:

pyenv shell 3.13.3
python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
python generate_bingo_card.py --output my-bingo-card.png

Run it from the BingoBot folder with this command:

python generate_bingo_card.py --output my-bingo-card.png

The script now creates two files by default:

- PNG card image (for sharing or archiving)
- Interactive HTML card that opens in your browser

In the web card, there is a Players sidebar on the left.
It starts with one permanent editable player (name + color), and you can add more players.
Select an active player, then click squares to shade them using that player's color. Click again to unmark.

By default, the center tile is a traditional free middle space.
Use --no-free-center if you want the center tile filled from your challenge lists.

If the output file already exists, the script moves the old image into the Old Generations folder before saving the new one.

The bot now mixes entries from Challenge.txt and Hard-Challenge.txt. It picks a random valid number of hard challenges and places them so every row, column, and diagonal bingo contains at least 1 hard challenge and no more than 2.

Optional flags:

--seed 42 for repeatable output
--template Bingo-Card-Template.jpg to use a different template
--challenges Challenge.txt to use a different list
--hard-challenges Hard-Challenge.txt to use a different hard challenge list
--padding 18 to adjust spacing inside each square
--archive-dir "Old Generations" to change where old images are stored
--web-output generated-bingo-card.html to change the interactive web card file name
--no-open-browser to generate the HTML file without automatically opening it
--free-center to use a free middle tile (default)
--no-free-center to force a list-generated center tile

Realtime hosting for other players:

1. Generate the card HTML:
python generate_bingo_card.py --output my-bingo-card.png --web-output generated-bingo-card.html --no-open-browser

2. Start the multiplayer server:
python realtime_server.py --web-card generated-bingo-card.html --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000

3. Share the link with players on your network:
http://YOUR-IP:8000/

Optional: use rooms in the URL query string so multiple games can run on one server:
http://YOUR-IP:8000/?room=my-game-night

When one player edits names/colors or marks/unmarks squares, everyone in the same room sees updates in real time.

Password-protected rooms:

- Enter a room name and password in the page, then click Join Room.
- The first successful join sets that room's password for the life of the server process.
- Other players must join the same room name with the same password.
- Copy Room Link copies only the room URL. Share the password separately.